<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="101" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="34.[227,348,1109,1135]" box="[227,348,1109,1135]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,348,1109,1135]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,348,1109,1135]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[227,1438,1157,1364]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miller, Dunbar &amp; Condra" authorityYear="1933" box="[368,539,1158,1183]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[368,539,1158,1183]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Maccoyoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reaching about 
<quantity box="[745,849,1157,1184]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="100.0">100 mm</quantity>
conch diameter. Conch with weakly depressed whorl profile (ww/wh ~1.10); venter flattened, ventrolateral shoulder narrowly subangular. Whorls just touching the preceding. Ornament in the juvenile stage with few coarse, granulated spiral lines on the flank, in the adult stage without spiral lines. Fine, sharp growth lines on the flank, with weakly biconvex course with a shallow lateral sinus and a moderately high ventrolateral projection. Venter with delicate growth lines with deep sinus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
