<subSubSection lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="34.[227,372,1741,1767]" box="[227,372,1741,1767]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,372,1741,1767]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,372,1741,1767]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[225,1436,1788,1960]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">
<typeStatus box="[227,336,1789,1815]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Holotype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30485 is an incomplete specimen with 
<quantity box="[888,972,1788,1815]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="66.0">66 mm</quantity>
conch diameter (
<figureCitation box="[1178,1267,1789,1815]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="35.[227,270,1105,1131]" captionTargetBox="[233,1435,510,1057]" captionTargetId="figure-224@35.[227,1437,504,1069]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Fig. 28. Maccoyoceras habadraense sp. nov., holotype MB.C.30485 (Korn et al. 2002 Coll.) from Hassi Habadra. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885266" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885266/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). It allows the study from both sides. The conch is extremely discoidal (ww/dm= 0.34) and evolute (uw/dm =0.46) with a high coiling rate (WER =2.17). The whorl profile is weakly depressed hexagonal (ww/wh =0.93) and widest at the rounded umbilical margin. The flanks converge barely towards the subangular ventrolateral shoulder that separates the flanks from the flattened venter. The umbilical wall is convexly rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[227,1436,2000,2027]" lastBlockId="34.[227,1436,2036,2063]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">
There are two ontogenetic stages in the ornament development; the first ranges up to about 
<quantity box="[1279,1360,2000,2027]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="35.0">35 mm</quantity>
conch diameter and possesses about ten spiral lines on the flank. The second stage does not show spirals but
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[227,752,229,255]" box="[227,837,229,256]" lastBlockId="35.[447,837,230,256]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">
<bibCitation box="[227,837,229,256]" journal="European Journal of Taxonomy" page="67" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" score="32.06971554747712" volume="831" year="2022">
<emphasis box="[227,597,229,256]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">European Journal of Taxonomy</emphasis>
831: 67–108 (2022)
</bibCitation>
</paragraph>
<caption box="[227,1256,302,329]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" startId="35.[227,296,302,328]">
<paragraph blockId="35.[227,1256,302,329]" box="[227,1256,302,329]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,340,302,328]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">Table 16.</emphasis>
Conch dimensions (in mm) and ratios of 
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[829,1159,302,328]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="habadraense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[829,1159,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">Maccoyoceras habadraense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1166,1256,303,329]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="35.[234,1414,374,447]" box="[268,1414,374,398]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[268,1414,374,398]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">Specimen dm ww wh uw ah ww/dm ww/wh uw/dm WER IZW</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[234,1414,374,447]" box="[234,1410,423,447]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">MB.C.30485 65.5 22.4 21.0 30.0 21.0 0.34 1.07 0.46 2.17 0.00</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885266" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6885266" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885266/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" startId="35.[227,270,1105,1131]" targetBox="[233,1435,510,1057]" targetPageId="35">
<paragraph blockId="35.[226,1436,1105,1167]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,318,1105,1131]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">Fig. 28.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[324,653,1105,1131]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="habadraense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,653,1105,1131]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">Maccoyoceras habadraense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[659,751,1106,1132]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype MB.C.30485 (Korn 
<emphasis box="[1104,1155,1105,1131]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">et al</emphasis>
. 2002 Coll.) from Hassi Habadra. Scale bar units =1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="35.[227,1436,1222,1284]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">only fine, narrow-standing growth lines with weakly biconvex course. These are restricted to the flanks, while the venter shows very delicate growth lines forming a very deep sinus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[227,341,1323,1349]" box="[227,341,1323,1349]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,341,1323,1349]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,341,1323,1349]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[227,1437,1369,1501]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,560,1369,1395]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="habadraense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,560,1369,1395]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">Maccoyoceras habadraense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[569,662,1370,1396]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has similarities with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korn, Miao &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[924,1109,1370,1395]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pentagonum">
<emphasis box="[924,1109,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">M. pentagonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but has a wider umbilicus (uw/dm = 
<quantity box="[344,429,1404,1431]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.143" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" unit="in" value="0.45">0.45 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[433,626,1404,1430]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="habadraense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[433,626,1404,1430]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">M. habadraense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[640,733,1405,1431]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
but only 
<quantity box="[853,937,1404,1431]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" unit="in" value="0.4">0.40 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korn, Miao &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[947,1134,1405,1430]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pentagonum">
<emphasis box="[947,1134,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">M. pentagonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Furthermore, the spiral lines are markedly coarser in 
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[582,774,1440,1466]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="habadraense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[582,774,1440,1466]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">M. habadraense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[783,873,1440,1466]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; this feature also distinguishes the new species from the other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
